f=Engineering/raj/marketplace/api-design-principles/SKILL.md · h1:API Design Principles=REST GraphQL design principles intuitive, scalable, maintainable APIs. · wu:This Skill=Designing new REST GraphQL APIs, Refactoring existing APIs better usability, Reviewing API specifications before implementation, Migrating between API paradigms (REST GraphQL), Optimizing APIs specific consumers (mobile, third-party) · h3:RESTful Design=`# Good: resource-oriented \· GET    /api/users              # list (paginated) \· POST   /api/users              # create \· GET    /api/users/{id}         # fetch \· PATCH  /api/users/{id}         # partial update` · h3:RESTful Design=**Resource-oriented architecture:** resources nouns (users, orders), never verbs; HTTP methods carry action; URLs represent hierarchies; naming consistent (plural nouns collections). **Method semantics:** `GET` retrieve (idempotent, safe) `POST` create `PUT` replace whole resource (idempotent) `PATCH` partial update `DELETE` remove (idempotent). · h3:GraphQL Design=Schema-first: types define domain model; queries read, mutations write, subscriptions stream. Clients request exactly what they need through one strongly-typed endpoint. · h3:Versioning Strategies=URL (`/api/v1/users`) header (`Accept: application/vnd.api+json; version=1`) query param. **Which strategy business uses set raj's `api-standards`** skill catalogs options. Plan breaking changes day one. · h2:REST Patterns=**Pagination filtering:** collection endpoint takes `page`/`page_size` (bounded, e.g. max 100) plus typed filter params; responses carry `items, total, page, pages` clients derive has-next/has-prev. **Errors status codes:** one structured error shape everywhere `error, message, details, timestamp, path` correct codes (400 validation, 401/403 auth, 404 missing, 409 conflict, 422 unprocessable, 5xx server). canonical shape lives `api-standards`; validation errors enumerate per-field problems. **HATEOAS (optional):** responses embed `_links` (self, related resources, allowed actions) clients navigate hypermedia instead hard-coded URLs. Adopt consumer benefits it's trade-off, default. · h2:GraphQL Patterns=**Schema design:** explicit object types relationships; Relay-style cursor pagination (`Connection`/`Edge`/`PageInfo`/`totalCount`); enums closed value sets; custom scalars (`DateTime`, `Money`); mutations take `input` types return payload types carrying `errors: [Error!]` structured failure. **Resolvers:** paginate cursors (fetch limit+1 derive `hasNextPage`); validate inputs schema resolver level; return errors mutation payloads, thrown exceptions. **DataLoader (N+1 prevention):** batch per-request loaders keyed one query parents' children, results mapped back input order. Any list field resolving relationship needs one. (Runtime N+1 symptoms dana's `db-performance`, joint fix.) · h2:Best Practices=**REST:** plural-noun collections stateless requests correct status codes version day one always paginate rate-limit OpenAPI/Swagger docs. **GraphQL:** schema before resolvers DataLoaders everywhere structured mutation errors cursor pagination (Relay spec) `@deprecated` directive gradual migration track query complexity execution time. · h2:Common Pitfalls=Over/under-fetching (REST GraphQL fixes requires DataLoaders) unversioned breaking changes inconsistent error formats missing rate limits POST idempotent operations **API structure mirroring database schema** (couples consumers internals model domain, tables). · b:with other skills=**api-standards (raj, custom):** CONTRACT authority auth-everywhere, versioning policy, one error shape, bounded responses, contract tests. skill informs design; api-standards decides. Conflicts api-standards., **service-patterns (raj):** resilience behind contract (idempotency, timeouts, breakers, queues)., **data-access-discipline (raj) db-performance (dana):** N+1 read-shaping data layer; DataLoader skill's edge-side half fix., **data-modeling (dana):** domain schema APIs express without mirroring storage., **git-workflow-and-versioning (dev):** semver judgment API-visible changes (Hyrum's Law: observed behavior contract)., **stack-profile (dev):** binds framework examples (FastAPI/Express/Ariadne/etc.) business., **Security Charter:** senior; API authn/authz gaps found review route aegis.